WEBVTT

00:56.598 --> 00:58.141
Talk about finding joy in the mundane.

00:58.600 --> 01:00.143
Having a drink with a friend after work.

01:01.144 --> 01:02.270
Isn't it just perfect?

01:02.479 --> 01:04.731
It'd be even better
if it was with a boyfriend.

01:05.190 --> 01:06.149
I don't agree.

01:07.233 --> 01:08.485
Then give me your boyfriend.

01:09.277 --> 01:10.820
I'll give you this in exchange.

01:11.654 --> 01:13.031
Hey, Yeong-ju. Seriously!

01:15.950 --> 01:16.785
Hey!

01:16.868 --> 01:20.080
EPISODE 1

01:33.593 --> 01:36.012
Hey, do you still have
the kimchi you gave me last time?

01:36.095 --> 01:37.722
I'm bringing it now.

01:38.765 --> 01:40.225
I hear a phone vibrating. It's yours.

01:40.308 --> 01:41.476
- Mine?
- Yes.

01:48.608 --> 01:51.027
- Hi, Gi-seok.
- Hey, are you still there?

01:52.487 --> 01:54.489
No, I'm at Yeong-ju's place
for another round.

01:54.823 --> 01:56.783
I see. When are you going home, then?

01:58.201 --> 02:00.745
In a bit, I guess? I'll just sleep here
if I end up staying late.

02:02.330 --> 02:04.207
Do you have an afternoon shift tomorrow?

02:05.083 --> 02:07.502
Yes. But it's Saturday,
so I have to be there before lunchtime.

02:07.585 --> 02:09.129
- Okay.
- Is your team dinner over?

02:10.088 --> 02:11.714
They want to go elsewhere for more drinks,

02:11.798 --> 02:14.008
but I'm playing basketball tomorrow,
so I'm going home.

02:14.551 --> 02:17.762
I got invited to the basketball club
started by my fellow college alumni.

02:18.763 --> 02:20.682
Oh, really? You should go, then.

02:21.724 --> 02:23.268
All right. I'll talk to you tomorrow.

02:23.643 --> 02:25.145
- Okay, bye.
- Bye.

02:32.152 --> 02:33.069
What?

02:33.153 --> 02:36.614
You guys are in a relationship.
Don't all couples say things like

02:36.739 --> 02:39.159
"I love you" to each other
before hanging up?

02:39.242 --> 02:40.577
Cut it out.

02:41.995 --> 02:43.746
This is why
long-term relationships are bad.

02:44.414 --> 02:46.583
Hey, it depends on the person.

02:46.958 --> 02:49.794
We were never lovey-dovey
even at the beginning. You know that.

02:50.044 --> 02:53.214
Right, you two have always been
like a middle-aged couple.

02:53.923 --> 02:54.966
We're not that bad.

02:56.217 --> 02:57.635
I've never envied your relationship.

02:58.761 --> 02:59.929
You told me to hand him over.

03:01.222 --> 03:02.348
You can keep him.

03:03.391 --> 03:04.392
- Jeez.
- Cheers.

03:05.268 --> 03:06.436
Cheers.

04:27.684 --> 04:29.852
- Good. That was great.
- Great job.

04:29.936 --> 04:32.230
You guys did well. Okay.

04:32.480 --> 04:34.023
- Good job.
- Well done. Good shot!

04:34.107 --> 04:36.276
- That was good. Great job.
- Thank you.

04:37.694 --> 04:38.611
Oh, boy.

04:39.570 --> 04:41.698
- Keep it up. For just a few more minutes.
- You did well.

04:41.781 --> 04:43.241
You're doing great. Keep it up.

04:43.366 --> 04:44.742
You're playing man-to-man defense?

04:44.826 --> 04:45.952
Slow down, okay?

04:46.035 --> 04:48.246
Remember to set a solid off-ball screen
and move faster.

04:48.329 --> 04:50.290
- That pass was good.
- Yes, okay.

04:51.207 --> 04:54.085
Guys. The defenders keep moving, you know.

04:54.168 --> 04:55.712
- Yes.
- You need to keep up with them.

04:56.212 --> 04:57.547
- I have to go.
- You're leaving?

04:57.630 --> 04:58.840
- Good job.
- Get going, then.

04:58.965 --> 05:00.717
- I'm off.
- See you. Great job today.

05:00.800 --> 05:02.135
- Bye.
- Good job, guys.

05:02.218 --> 05:04.554
- See you all next week.
- Focus on the game, okay?

05:04.637 --> 05:05.763
I'm off, guys.

05:05.847 --> 05:07.098
- Bye.
- See you next week.

05:07.181 --> 05:09.142
- Come next week.
- Hey, I'm leaving.

05:09.309 --> 05:12.270
Hey, wait. This is Gi-seok.
I've told you about him before.

05:12.353 --> 05:13.688
He helped us rent this gym today.

05:14.772 --> 05:16.691
- This is the friend I told you about.
- I see.

05:16.774 --> 05:18.359
You probably don't remember him.

05:19.819 --> 05:22.780
I feel like I've seen him before,
but why don't I remember him?

05:23.990 --> 05:25.616
Did you also start your undergrad in 2004?

05:26.200 --> 05:27.869
Yes, that's right. I'm Yu Ji-ho.

05:27.952 --> 05:29.787
Nice to meet you. I'm Kwon Gi-seok.

05:30.872 --> 05:34.250
Jeez, look at you. He's younger than you.

05:34.500 --> 05:37.879
Don't be so polite during the games.
Just crush them down.

05:38.504 --> 05:39.672
Especially this dude.

05:40.381 --> 05:42.258
When it comes to basketball,
he's such a snob.

05:42.341 --> 05:43.718
You are no match for me.

05:44.969 --> 05:46.054
Look at that.

05:46.512 --> 05:49.474
This is exciting.
Let's play together next time.

05:49.557 --> 05:51.851
Yes, of course.
I won't go easy on you though.

05:52.560 --> 05:53.853
You shouldn't.

05:55.897 --> 05:57.565
- I'll be off, then. Bye.
- Bye.

05:59.108 --> 06:00.026
Let's go, Gi-seok.

07:32.577 --> 07:35.204
WOORI PHARMACY

07:35.288 --> 07:36.664
- Hello.
- Hello.

07:38.541 --> 07:40.042
Do you have any medicine for hangovers?

07:42.128 --> 07:43.212
I need something strong.

07:47.175 --> 07:49.427
This will help too. You can have a sip.

07:49.844 --> 07:51.554
Okay, thank you.

08:03.649 --> 08:07.987
If you have any rubber bands
lying around, could I please get one?

08:12.116 --> 08:14.368
- This is all I have.
- That's exactly what I need.

08:15.036 --> 08:16.037
Thank you.

08:23.586 --> 08:24.921
Oh, here.

08:39.727 --> 08:40.978
What's my total?

08:41.062 --> 08:42.605
- It's 6,000 won.
- Okay.

08:47.485 --> 08:48.569
Where's my wallet?

08:53.533 --> 08:54.492
Where did it go?

08:55.451 --> 08:57.787
- Did you lose your wallet?
- No. This is so weird.

08:58.496 --> 08:59.830
Last night, I...

09:00.456 --> 09:02.208
Never mind. Just a second, please.

09:17.098 --> 09:21.185
Well, it looks like I left it
at my friend's place. What should I do?

09:21.269 --> 09:22.812
Where is your friend's place?

09:24.021 --> 09:25.523
She lives over there.

09:26.357 --> 09:28.985
- Are you sure your wallet is there?
- I'm pretty sure...

09:29.986 --> 09:32.113
No, I know that it's there.

09:33.155 --> 09:34.532
Just a moment, please.

09:46.669 --> 09:48.921
- What's my total again?
- It's 6,000 won.

09:51.424 --> 09:52.717
Gosh, why isn't she picking up?

09:54.260 --> 09:57.096
I'm in a rush now.
So I'll come back in the evening and...

09:57.179 --> 09:59.473
Actually, my friend is still asleep.

09:59.557 --> 10:02.351
- As soon as she wakes up, I'll tell her--
- You can just go.

10:02.935 --> 10:05.396
No, I need to settle up.

10:06.856 --> 10:09.692
Give me your account number.
Then I can send it to you right away.

10:09.775 --> 10:12.194
No, just go. You said
you'll settle up next time. Just do that.

10:14.947 --> 10:16.032
I'm sorry.

10:17.158 --> 10:18.909
I promise I'll come back and settle up.

10:28.878 --> 10:29.879
Actually, excuse me.

10:31.672 --> 10:32.673
It's not like I opened it.

10:33.716 --> 10:35.926
- Pardon?
- You opened that new bottle.

10:36.177 --> 10:38.012
I never said I wanted to drink it.

10:40.389 --> 10:41.849
You asked for a hangover remedy.

10:41.932 --> 10:43.434
Right, I did.

10:43.517 --> 10:46.979
But I never asked you
to open the bottle and mix it for me.

10:49.398 --> 10:50.441
Right, I made a mistake.

10:52.902 --> 10:53.903
You said you're in a rush.

10:56.656 --> 10:58.115
Shall I give you my number?

11:00.701 --> 11:01.661
I mean, just in case.

11:03.412 --> 11:05.539
I'll definitely come back and settle up,

11:05.790 --> 11:07.792
but just in case you don't trust me.

11:09.919 --> 11:12.296
It's hard to trust people these days,
so I understand.

11:17.551 --> 11:18.427
Zero, one, zero.

11:20.888 --> 11:22.098
Four, five, nine, three...

11:34.235 --> 11:35.111
Hey.

11:43.452 --> 11:44.870
Oh, you don't have to do this.

11:46.038 --> 11:47.164
Do you need more?

11:49.125 --> 11:51.210
I'm not giving you this money.

11:52.169 --> 11:53.045
Pay me back.

11:55.423 --> 11:56.298
What is your name?

11:59.135 --> 12:01.387
I'm Yu Ji-ho.

12:03.472 --> 12:04.473
I'm Lee Jeong-in.

12:06.517 --> 12:09.228
Be safe, Ms. Lee Jeong-in.

12:24.577 --> 12:26.495
It's in the bag
from the convenience store.

12:27.288 --> 12:29.915
You bought the beer last night.
I guess that's when you put it there.

12:31.125 --> 12:33.919
Hey, I'll either pick it up after work
or if I get off too late...

12:34.795 --> 12:35.963
Anyway, hold on to it.

12:37.173 --> 12:38.757
How will you pay for the taxi ride?

12:40.926 --> 12:43.721
I'll call Ha-rin and ask her to come down.

12:46.557 --> 12:49.018
Hey, if you pass by the pharmacy...

12:49.977 --> 12:50.978
Never mind.

12:51.604 --> 12:53.939
Pharmacy? Why? Are you feeling sick?

12:55.149 --> 12:57.776
No, I'm fine.
Anyway, hold on to my wallet, okay?

12:58.152 --> 12:59.069
Bye.

13:09.580 --> 13:11.957
ADD NEW CONTACT

13:18.339 --> 13:19.381
I memorized it.

13:23.844 --> 13:27.348
The elevated levels
of fine particulate matter have dropped,

13:27.431 --> 13:29.517
so you can enjoy being outdoors
this weekend.

13:29.600 --> 13:31.101
However, you should still wear a mask

13:31.185 --> 13:33.562
when you go outside
for your health's sake.

13:34.522 --> 13:36.023
That's it for the 12 p.m. news update.

13:36.106 --> 13:38.067
Thank you all for watching.

13:42.279 --> 13:43.197
- Good work.
- Thank you.

13:45.115 --> 13:46.534
- Great job!
- Good work, everyone.

13:48.494 --> 13:50.663
- Great job.
- Well done, everyone.

13:54.708 --> 13:56.752
Don't touch any of my stuff.

14:05.928 --> 14:07.221
What a cheeky...

15:06.030 --> 15:07.698
This is getting rid of my hangover.

15:12.202 --> 15:15.456
It's not getting rid of mine.
I think I drank way too much last night.

15:16.123 --> 15:17.124
Really?

15:21.837 --> 15:23.547
I wish meeting people
could be like this too.

15:24.048 --> 15:27.509
I want to meet people who continue to grow
on me even though I had no expectations.

15:29.219 --> 15:32.806
The first encounter could be all you need
to be smitten by someone, like destiny.

15:33.349 --> 15:34.308
My goodness.

15:34.975 --> 15:37.353
You don't even believe in horoscopes.
What's gotten into you?

15:38.187 --> 15:40.397
Well, that makes me feel
as if I'm being brainwashed.

15:40.564 --> 15:43.025
"Don't do this. Don't go there."
I don't like it.

15:43.108 --> 15:45.110
But it's not like you enjoy adventure.

15:46.487 --> 15:49.073
Hey, who even gets a chance
to be adventurous?

15:49.156 --> 15:51.575
You go to school, get your degree,
and get a job.

15:51.992 --> 15:53.285
After that, all you do is work

15:53.369 --> 15:54.954
and hang out with friends here and there.

15:55.037 --> 15:56.372
Why leave out dating?

15:56.747 --> 15:58.540
It's the cause of all sorts of problems.

16:01.794 --> 16:04.838
Thankfully,
even that aspect of my life has been

16:05.798 --> 16:07.174
relatively problem-free.

16:07.841 --> 16:10.177
I don't like to be in a relationship
that is too boring.

16:11.845 --> 16:14.098
- "Boring"?
- Yes.

16:15.265 --> 16:16.266
I don't like it.

16:18.978 --> 16:20.020
Just a second.

16:21.981 --> 16:24.024
- Hey.
- What account number?

16:25.359 --> 16:26.276
What?

16:26.944 --> 16:29.279
Your message.
You asked for my account number.

16:30.197 --> 16:33.200
Oh, that. It was for someone else.

16:33.283 --> 16:35.160
I guess I sent it to you by mistake.
I'm sorry.

16:36.662 --> 16:37.997
- For whom?
- What?

16:39.039 --> 16:40.124
Who was it for?

16:43.377 --> 16:45.045
One of my clients. A publishing firm.

16:55.097 --> 16:56.390
Thank you.

17:32.968 --> 17:34.970
PHARMACIST
YOUR BANK ACCOUNT NUMBER!

18:34.154 --> 18:35.447
Hurry up.

18:45.332 --> 18:46.500
- This is...
- What?

18:47.835 --> 18:50.587
- I'm like this too though.
- What did you say?

18:50.921 --> 18:52.631
Don't worry. It looks fine.

18:54.466 --> 18:55.801
Security activated.

19:04.560 --> 19:05.978
How's the new department?

19:08.105 --> 19:10.107
It's the evaluation team,
so the workload is high.

19:10.190 --> 19:11.942
And I'll be away
from the office quite often.

19:13.944 --> 19:16.613
I thought you worked at your desk all day
since you work for a bank.

19:18.365 --> 19:20.409
Anyway, that means you'll be even busier
from now on.

19:22.703 --> 19:24.371
That being said...

19:24.997 --> 19:25.998
Yes?

19:27.374 --> 19:29.793
Shouldn't we start talking
about getting married?

19:33.672 --> 19:36.216
- Why are you surprised?
- I'm not surprised.

19:37.134 --> 19:38.427
I mean, we should get married.

19:43.765 --> 19:44.933
Why are you all quiet?

19:46.059 --> 19:47.269
What do you want to hear?

19:48.896 --> 19:50.314
What now?

19:51.064 --> 19:52.191
What do you mean, "What now?"

19:58.447 --> 19:59.823
Did you tell Yeong-ju to come out?

20:01.074 --> 20:02.367
I texted her just now.

20:03.535 --> 20:04.828
You two can have dinner together.

20:06.413 --> 20:07.497
What about you?

20:08.498 --> 20:11.460
I was going to go home
and get some work done if she's free.

20:12.127 --> 20:13.712
I need to get the hang of my new tasks.

20:14.671 --> 20:17.466
Then just go home.
I don't have much of an appetite anyway.

20:17.716 --> 20:20.302
I'm not saying I don't have time
to have dinner with you.

20:20.385 --> 20:21.595
Let's grab a bite together.

20:21.762 --> 20:24.348
- It's okay.
- What is okay?

20:25.098 --> 20:26.225
I said it's okay.

20:28.393 --> 20:29.645
Jeez, forget it.

20:30.979 --> 20:32.022
What?

20:33.023 --> 20:35.025
Why are you sulking over nothing?

20:35.609 --> 20:36.693
Who's sulking?

20:37.444 --> 20:38.904
I know you well enough, okay?

20:42.908 --> 20:44.201
Seriously.

20:46.536 --> 20:49.414
WOORI PHARMACY

21:01.677 --> 21:02.719
- Hello.
- Hello.

21:04.471 --> 21:06.807
- Thanks.
- You seem a little down.

21:07.975 --> 21:09.601
It'd be nice to grab dinner together.

21:10.185 --> 21:12.312
I already got food
from the convenience store.

21:13.814 --> 21:14.940
Why are you downcast?

21:16.316 --> 21:17.901
- Did you two fight?
- Should we fight?

21:18.986 --> 21:19.820
I hope you win.

21:20.654 --> 21:21.780
I'm off.

21:27.703 --> 21:28.787
- I'll call you later.
- Okay.

21:35.711 --> 21:36.795
Hey, what are you doing?

21:37.796 --> 21:38.797
I'm coming.

21:49.641 --> 21:51.018
You're so slow.

21:52.019 --> 21:54.396
Dude, you always lose
when we play basketball together.

21:56.148 --> 21:57.941
He's boasting
after winning just a few times.

21:58.650 --> 21:59.943
Hey, you've met Gi-seok.

22:00.360 --> 22:02.863
If he joins my team, you'll be done for.
Game over.

22:03.530 --> 22:04.489
Who is he?

22:04.823 --> 22:06.867
I told you one of my co-workers
is our fellow alumnus.

22:07.075 --> 22:08.785
He helped us rent the school gym today.

22:09.453 --> 22:11.663
His father is the chairman
of the foundation.

22:12.372 --> 22:14.041
- I envy him.
- Oh, right.

22:15.167 --> 22:17.961
His girlfriend's dad is the principal
of that school. I heard she's hot.

22:21.298 --> 22:23.967
Hey, seriously. How can life be so unfair?

22:24.885 --> 22:26.595
- It pisses me off.
- You've never seen her?

22:27.179 --> 22:28.263
No, never.

22:29.473 --> 22:32.392
But I want to arrange something soon.

22:33.101 --> 22:36.730
After that, I'll set you two up
with girls. That's the plan.

22:38.190 --> 22:40.442
Hey, I have to study.

22:41.443 --> 22:42.444
Oh, right.

22:42.611 --> 22:45.030
As for you, we'll wait
until you pass the civil service exam.

22:46.406 --> 22:47.532
But you're on board, right?

22:48.492 --> 22:49.659
I'll figure it out myself.

22:50.327 --> 22:51.495
What?

22:52.287 --> 22:54.331
You're so busted. You'd better tell us.

22:55.207 --> 22:57.793
Tell us already.
You're seeing someone, aren't you?

22:58.460 --> 22:59.836
No, not at all.

23:00.420 --> 23:01.797
I should go bring some beer.

23:04.174 --> 23:06.843
Hey, you're stuck in the pharmacy all day.

23:06.927 --> 23:09.971
And all you do on weekends is play
basketball. What is wrong with you?

23:10.555 --> 23:12.933
You should meet girls
whenever you get a chance. Date anyone--

23:13.016 --> 23:14.935
Gosh, he said he'll figure it out himself.

23:15.310 --> 23:17.062
I'd love to see him figuring it out.

23:17.229 --> 23:18.855
I mean,
it's not like he committed a crime.

23:20.023 --> 23:21.858
Hey, please.

23:23.693 --> 23:25.112
What? We're friends.

23:26.446 --> 23:27.614
Hey, did I offend you?

23:28.198 --> 23:29.241
Whatever.

23:29.658 --> 23:32.410
Hey, the meat will burn.
There's more beer, so drink up.

23:33.245 --> 23:34.079
Here.

23:46.174 --> 23:48.218
I said we should have dinner together.
How stubborn.

23:48.927 --> 23:50.137
Don't put the blame on me.

23:53.723 --> 23:55.267
We should move in together soon.

23:59.146 --> 24:00.981
This won't happen if we live together.

24:02.440 --> 24:03.859
We'd eat, sleep,

24:03.942 --> 24:06.027
go home, and go to work together.
It'll be convenient.

24:07.320 --> 24:09.698
So, you want to marry me to avoid hassles?

24:10.991 --> 24:13.410
Why do you keep putting words in my mouth?

24:14.369 --> 24:15.495
Then what is it?

24:17.998 --> 24:19.166
What can I do?

24:19.583 --> 24:20.792
How can I make you feel better?

24:21.877 --> 24:23.086
You said you know me well.

24:24.087 --> 24:25.213
What can I do?

24:28.133 --> 24:29.634
Get out of my sight at once.

24:31.678 --> 24:33.013
I will if you get out.

24:35.765 --> 24:36.766
All right.

24:39.019 --> 24:40.103
Okay, I heard you.

24:41.980 --> 24:43.565
I'll make it up to you next weekend.

24:44.983 --> 24:46.193
Think of what you want to do.

24:47.903 --> 24:48.904
Just go.

24:52.365 --> 24:53.617
Sweet dreams.

25:21.019 --> 25:22.103
My gosh.

25:27.442 --> 25:28.526
Is that you, Jae-in?

25:30.570 --> 25:32.322
- Jeong-in.
- What's going on?

25:32.989 --> 25:34.157
When did you get here?

25:34.741 --> 25:35.909
What's up with this...

25:36.701 --> 25:37.827
Does Mom know you're here?

25:38.036 --> 25:40.747
Can we talk inside?
Gosh, I'm so cold and hungry.

25:42.040 --> 25:43.124
You're unbelievable.

25:44.084 --> 25:46.086
- Let's talk inside.
- Okay.

26:07.899 --> 26:10.485
I was such a great photographer
even back then.

26:10.568 --> 26:12.070
Both of you look amazing in this photo.

26:12.654 --> 26:13.905
Come here and eat this.

26:14.572 --> 26:15.573
Okay!

26:16.241 --> 26:17.951
Thank you.

26:30.630 --> 26:31.840
It's so good.

26:34.009 --> 26:35.719
First, tell me what happened.

26:36.511 --> 26:38.430
Hold on. Let me have some kimchi first.

26:41.141 --> 26:42.350
What? It's not Mom's kimchi.

26:43.601 --> 26:44.769
Come on. Tell me.

26:45.812 --> 26:46.896
Not much happened.

26:48.440 --> 26:49.899
I had chased a guy for a while,

26:50.567 --> 26:53.820
but he reported me
to the police as a stalker,

26:53.903 --> 26:55.238
so I got a restraining order.

26:55.947 --> 26:58.033
- You?
- Yes, me.

26:59.367 --> 27:02.120
Stalking is considered a serious crime
in France.

27:03.371 --> 27:05.498
I was afraid I'd keep
going there to see him.

27:06.374 --> 27:07.917
So I thought, "I should go back to Korea

27:08.001 --> 27:10.086
to avoid becoming a criminal."
That's why I'm here.

27:11.296 --> 27:12.630
So, you actually stalked him?

27:13.673 --> 27:16.051
I just asked him to marry me
a few times, and he overreacted.

27:16.384 --> 27:18.720
Marry you?
Jae-in, have you lost your mind?

27:19.304 --> 27:21.473
Love incapacitates your logical brain.

27:21.556 --> 27:24.184
You call that love?
You're seriously crazy.

27:24.434 --> 27:25.477
Love makes you crazy.

27:38.740 --> 27:39.991
How's your relationship?

27:41.785 --> 27:42.827
Not bad.

27:46.039 --> 27:46.998
What?

27:52.379 --> 27:53.213
This is delicious.

28:52.689 --> 28:53.898
CHATS

28:53.982 --> 28:57.777
LEE JEONG-IN
YOUR BANK ACCOUNT NUMBER!

29:52.248 --> 29:53.458
ALARM WILL GO OFF IN TWO DAYS

29:53.541 --> 29:55.210
ALARM IS SET FOR 7:30 A.M.,
MONDAY, MARCH 11

29:55.293 --> 29:56.586
GI-SEOK

29:56.669 --> 29:58.505
Don't eat the whole thing.
You'll gain weight.

30:06.471 --> 30:07.847
CHATS

30:07.931 --> 30:10.391
PHARMACIST
YOUR BANK ACCOUNT NUMBER!

30:36.292 --> 30:38.753
- Drive safely.
- Thank you. Take care.

31:14.706 --> 31:15.999
- You're still up.
- Yes.

31:17.584 --> 31:20.003
- What brings you here this late?
- I was in the area.

31:21.379 --> 31:22.797
- Have you eaten?
- Yes, I have.

31:23.423 --> 31:24.632
You'll sleep here, right?

31:24.883 --> 31:27.552
I have to leave early in the morning,
so don't mind me and go to bed.

32:01.878 --> 32:02.962
Daddy.

32:05.590 --> 32:06.841
What are you doing here?

32:08.593 --> 32:11.012
I came to see you
because I suddenly started missing you.

32:12.430 --> 32:14.807
- Did you not miss me?
- I missed you.

32:16.100 --> 32:18.561
Oh, boy! Gosh, you'll beat me soon.

32:20.688 --> 32:23.066
- I'm stronger than you are.
- You are?

32:23.816 --> 32:24.817
Really?

32:26.778 --> 32:27.904
Why are you so strong?

32:30.865 --> 32:32.492
Here's your ox bone soup.

32:40.083 --> 32:41.417
- Enjoy.
- Hey.

32:42.919 --> 32:44.587
I went ahead and ordered to save time.

32:45.338 --> 32:46.506
Good call.

32:47.298 --> 32:48.466
Why did you have to go there?

32:49.509 --> 32:51.386
It's about the same thing
every single time.

32:52.178 --> 32:54.889
"Transparent management"
of the foundation and so on.

33:02.063 --> 33:03.564
So, how's the new department?

33:05.149 --> 33:06.234
Well...

33:07.235 --> 33:08.319
Not bad.

33:08.820 --> 33:11.447
Some at the executive level
used to work in the evaluation team.

33:13.491 --> 33:15.076
Start thinking about getting married.

33:17.453 --> 33:20.206
It'd be nice to focus on work
with your wife's support.

33:24.627 --> 33:28.172
Word has it that Assemblyman Jang
will be appointed Director of the FSS.

33:30.049 --> 33:31.342
His youngest daughter

33:32.260 --> 33:33.720
is so successful.

33:34.554 --> 33:37.557
It's not easy to become a professor
at such a young age.

33:38.474 --> 33:39.892
She's very impressive.

33:44.230 --> 33:45.815
Cut out people that you don't need.

33:49.027 --> 33:50.611
Jeong-in is a good girl.

33:52.447 --> 33:54.574
She's not the only "good girl."

33:55.992 --> 33:57.910
It's just not easy to find
the right one to marry.

33:59.871 --> 34:01.372
Don't leave it to the last minute.

34:02.874 --> 34:04.042
You should end it now.

34:07.170 --> 34:08.254
I'll figure out what to do.

34:10.423 --> 34:12.759
You'd better make the right decision.

34:21.893 --> 34:24.312
I'll arrange something
with Assemblyman Jang's family.

34:25.396 --> 34:26.355
Maybe later on.

34:28.524 --> 34:30.193
I told you that I'll figure it out.

34:32.278 --> 34:34.781
- I'll think hard about it.
- About what?

34:34.864 --> 34:37.950
Well, it's about my marriage.
I need to do some thinking.

34:38.618 --> 34:41.621
Marriage isn't some kids' role-play game.
It's a part of the business.

34:42.371 --> 34:43.581
Just remember that.

34:58.554 --> 35:01.808
SUYEONG HIGH SCHOOL

35:01.891 --> 35:06.354
PRINCIPAL LEE TAE-HAK

35:13.778 --> 35:17.406
ANYONE CAN EARN 5 MILLION WON A MONTH
WITHIN 5 YEARS OF RETIREMENT

35:21.244 --> 35:22.245
Come in.

35:27.166 --> 35:28.251
Mr. Kwon.

35:29.210 --> 35:31.212
I'm just stopping by on my way back.
Have a seat.

35:31.295 --> 35:35.675
- All right. Did you have to step out?
- Yes, to the Teachers' Pension Office.

35:36.259 --> 35:37.844
And I saw Gi-seok too.

35:37.927 --> 35:39.345
He works in that area, you know.

35:39.762 --> 35:42.431
Right. Come to think of it,
I haven't seen him in quite a while.

35:43.057 --> 35:44.183
Is he doing well?

35:44.851 --> 35:46.644
- He's well.
- Good.

35:48.604 --> 35:50.314
Gi-seok is a guy, so we're not in a rush,

35:50.398 --> 35:52.483
but shouldn't you rush
your daughter a little?

35:53.568 --> 35:54.694
Well, frankly...

35:55.778 --> 35:57.363
We are getting anxious.

35:58.990 --> 36:01.868
I think it's high time for us
to start discussing the topic.

36:02.869 --> 36:04.036
Does she want to get married?

36:04.120 --> 36:07.498
Yes, of course she does. They've been
together for a while, you know.

36:08.124 --> 36:09.792
They must be quite attached to each other.

36:10.710 --> 36:12.295
I don't think it's that serious.

36:12.378 --> 36:14.797
I wouldn't say they're "attached."

36:16.883 --> 36:19.802
Your eldest daughter married
a great guy. Jeong-in will do the same.

36:19.886 --> 36:20.970
I heard she's a great catch.

36:22.305 --> 36:23.347
Well, yes.

36:27.476 --> 36:29.228
Let's go for lunch tomorrow
or the day after.

36:32.481 --> 36:34.483
- Do you not want to?
- I do, of course.

36:35.902 --> 36:37.361
- I'll call you.
- Okay.

37:00.509 --> 37:03.304
WIFE

37:03.804 --> 37:05.348
You don't know what it's about?

37:06.891 --> 37:09.518
No, I'm not annoyed. Why does he
want me to come by out of the blue?

37:10.645 --> 37:13.522
Mom, tell Seo-in to come as well
so that she can join us for the meal.

37:15.191 --> 37:16.776
No, you do it. I'm busy now.

37:17.318 --> 37:18.402
Okay, bye.

37:25.493 --> 37:28.120
You look like you're going
to fight someone today.

37:28.371 --> 37:30.414
Hey, you're going home
right after work, right?

37:30.998 --> 37:33.042
Why? Shall I get booze ready
and wait for you again?

37:33.125 --> 37:34.418
Get a lot of booze.

37:35.336 --> 37:37.630
Gosh, I'm already scared.

37:37.713 --> 37:40.132
I should stop by the pharmacy
and get something for my liver.

37:41.968 --> 37:43.135
Do you go there often?

37:44.053 --> 37:45.137
The pharmacy? Which one?

37:45.471 --> 37:47.181
The one in your area, on your way home.

37:47.974 --> 37:49.141
Right, there is a pharmacy.

37:50.601 --> 37:52.144
You sound as if you're a regular there.

38:01.404 --> 38:02.655
It was a slip of the tongue.

38:03.447 --> 38:04.907
It didn't sound like that.

38:12.748 --> 38:13.833
What do you want?

38:14.125 --> 38:16.127
Did you run home to tell your mommy?

38:17.336 --> 38:19.088
Your mother asked me to come over.

38:19.839 --> 38:20.923
Then come.

38:22.550 --> 38:24.051
And be dragged to hell with you?

38:24.719 --> 38:27.138
Seo-in, what are you
trying to achieve by being cheeky?

38:27.722 --> 38:29.015
You seem scared.

38:30.766 --> 38:33.102
That smart brain of yours
must be on the fritz,

38:33.185 --> 38:35.604
but you're the one
with everything to lose here.

38:36.731 --> 38:38.691
- Whether you come or not is your choice.
- But...

38:42.486 --> 38:45.614
What am I going to do with her cheeky ass?

38:59.712 --> 39:02.214
- You're here.
- How could I not come when you asked?

39:02.298 --> 39:04.091
You're the best. Why weren't you inside?

39:04.842 --> 39:06.135
I had to take a call.

39:07.011 --> 39:09.513
- What do you think Dad wants?
- Who knows?

39:10.014 --> 39:12.308
Still, I can probably guess.

39:18.105 --> 39:21.692
Just being with you girls only
makes me miss Jae-in more.

39:25.237 --> 39:26.697
Seo-in, dig in already.

39:27.281 --> 39:29.367
You seem gaunt on TV these days.

39:29.450 --> 39:30.701
Are you on a diet again?

39:31.243 --> 39:32.078
No.

39:32.912 --> 39:34.413
Are you sick then?

39:34.705 --> 39:36.749
We should see a doctor tomorrow.

39:37.333 --> 39:39.502
Her husband's a doctor
and her in-laws own a hospital.

39:39.585 --> 39:40.878
You're overstepping.

39:42.463 --> 39:44.673
I'm not sick, Mom,
so please don't overstep.

39:46.133 --> 39:48.344
Is your husband busy?
He hasn't been over lately.

39:48.719 --> 39:50.262
He just started his night shifts.

39:50.930 --> 39:52.515
I heard he couldn't make time.

39:53.641 --> 39:56.268
He's back at 11 p.m. at the earliest
and I should be home by then.

39:56.685 --> 39:57.895
Should I tell him to come?

40:01.232 --> 40:02.775
So how's it going with Gi-seok?

40:05.152 --> 40:06.237
It's pretty much the same.

40:06.821 --> 40:08.364
So you'll just stick to dating him?

40:09.198 --> 40:11.117
Maybe, or I could even end it. Who knows?

40:12.284 --> 40:13.786
Are you kidding me?

40:14.453 --> 40:15.996
Why date someone you'll break up with?

40:16.664 --> 40:18.290
Should I call it quits then?

40:19.208 --> 40:20.376
Why are you being this way?

40:20.876 --> 40:22.378
Aren't you going to marry him?

40:23.546 --> 40:24.922
Who knows what will happen?

40:26.924 --> 40:29.260
What's going on?
Did you say something to her?

40:30.469 --> 40:32.096
I threatened her to stay unmarried.

40:34.932 --> 40:37.893
I don't care. Talk with Gi-seok
and set a date for this year.

40:41.355 --> 40:44.191
Stalling will only
make you lose out in the end.

40:47.736 --> 40:48.904
Seo-in, sorry about this.

40:50.781 --> 40:52.491
I won't be pushed into it like her.

40:53.701 --> 40:55.494
I want to weigh my options

40:55.578 --> 40:58.122
and get married on my own terms
when I'm ready.

40:58.998 --> 41:00.416
I don't know when it'll be though.

41:00.499 --> 41:02.835
Pushed? By whom?

41:04.128 --> 41:04.962
Seo-in, you tell me.

41:05.504 --> 41:07.298
Did I force you into this marriage?

41:07.381 --> 41:08.549
Did I?

41:10.134 --> 41:11.218
Yes.

41:13.596 --> 41:15.389
I'm not blaming you for it all.

41:16.098 --> 41:17.808
It's partly my fault as well.

41:20.811 --> 41:22.563
Are you two kidding me?

41:23.647 --> 41:24.940
Is marriage a joke to you?

41:26.942 --> 41:28.486
It seems to be to you.

41:29.236 --> 41:30.404
I'm an adult, Dad.

41:31.113 --> 41:34.283
Please respect my wishes
when it comes to my marriage.

41:53.344 --> 41:54.303
I'm sorry.

41:56.180 --> 41:59.934
It's true that your marriage
gave me clarity though.

42:01.852 --> 42:02.895
I know.

42:04.480 --> 42:05.689
Thanks for understanding.

42:10.778 --> 42:13.781
There's something I want you
to understand too.

42:16.909 --> 42:17.952
I'm...

42:19.537 --> 42:20.621
getting a divorce.

42:22.456 --> 42:23.707
Not any time soon,

42:24.500 --> 42:26.001
but we're no longer living together.

42:29.838 --> 42:31.549
Will you be all right though?

42:33.092 --> 42:34.927
Rumors spread fast these days

42:35.511 --> 42:36.887
and this will hurt your image.

42:37.972 --> 42:40.432
That's been holding me back all this time.

42:42.893 --> 42:43.936
The divorce...

42:44.812 --> 42:46.188
Did Si-hoon agree to it?

42:48.941 --> 42:50.359
I'll have to make sure that he does.

42:53.737 --> 42:54.822
Are you all right?

42:55.114 --> 42:57.283
Yes, for now at least.

42:59.702 --> 43:01.036
Can I help in any way?

43:04.123 --> 43:06.083
Just take my side when the time comes.

43:07.126 --> 43:08.752
I've always been on your side.

43:10.713 --> 43:12.131
Are you really all right though?

43:16.343 --> 43:17.761
Call me whenever you need to.

43:18.220 --> 43:19.805
I'll always be on standby.

43:20.347 --> 43:22.558
- You know that, right?
- Of course.

43:27.521 --> 43:28.856
We're all in such a mess.

43:31.650 --> 43:34.111
Jae-in is at my house.

43:37.239 --> 43:38.824
No news is never good news with her.

43:39.491 --> 43:40.534
Tell me about it.

43:41.327 --> 43:42.620
Let's get together soon.

43:43.454 --> 43:44.496
Unbelievable.

43:44.580 --> 43:47.166
Just so you know, we're in this together.

43:48.917 --> 43:50.461
It must be a sister thing.

43:50.919 --> 43:52.004
Goodness.

43:56.258 --> 43:58.385
Seo-in, you've got this.

44:05.309 --> 44:06.393
Thanks.

44:12.149 --> 44:13.192
Unbelievable.

44:18.155 --> 44:19.198
It's snowing!

44:20.032 --> 44:22.785
If only I had a date tonight. Damn it.

44:23.661 --> 44:25.704
- Why are you upset?
- Because it's snowing.

44:26.330 --> 44:28.040
I'm not going home early
on a day like this.

44:29.041 --> 44:31.585
- Is that a rule?
- When it's snowing, yes.

44:32.211 --> 44:33.337
Good night then.

44:34.213 --> 44:36.590
- Have you already made plans?
- I will on my way home.

44:36.924 --> 44:38.550
- See you tomorrow.
- Bye.

44:42.221 --> 44:43.347
You're here.

44:53.982 --> 44:55.692
Why didn't you text me
your account number?

44:59.154 --> 45:00.489
I asked you a question.

45:03.367 --> 45:05.035
So I can see you one more time like this.

45:09.248 --> 45:10.999
Can I get my change?

45:12.793 --> 45:14.086
Have you had dinner?

45:14.711 --> 45:16.547
If not, we could grab a bite with this.

45:19.383 --> 45:22.052
I don't like eating with strangers.

45:28.183 --> 45:29.309
What is it?

45:30.644 --> 45:32.146
You memorized my number,

45:33.021 --> 45:35.065
so how am I a stranger now?

45:38.610 --> 45:40.404
I have good memory, that's all.

45:41.530 --> 45:43.740
You're getting ahead of yourself

45:43.824 --> 45:46.452
if you thought it meant something more.

45:46.994 --> 45:48.912
It's not like we'll cross paths again.

45:52.583 --> 45:53.500
Take care then.

47:31.890 --> 47:33.850
So both your parents and his parents

47:33.934 --> 47:35.978
are starting to talk about you guys
getting married?

47:36.979 --> 47:39.147
I want to marry because I want to,

47:39.648 --> 47:41.316
not because I'm at that age.

47:44.111 --> 47:46.738
For you, logic always wins
but not when it comes to love.

47:47.739 --> 47:48.949
Charming, aren't I?

47:50.367 --> 47:51.535
That must be our chicken.

47:52.411 --> 47:53.453
- I'll get it.
- Thank you.

48:08.010 --> 48:09.595
How did you know I was here?

48:10.512 --> 48:11.638
Did you follow me?

48:14.516 --> 48:15.642
I don't need the change.

48:16.393 --> 48:17.394
Up here.

48:20.689 --> 48:21.732
Leave already!

48:22.274 --> 48:23.442
I'll call the cops.

48:25.527 --> 48:26.737
Thank you.

48:27.904 --> 48:29.781
- Bye.
- Goodbye.

48:55.641 --> 48:57.267
What took you so long?

48:58.685 --> 48:59.770
It's nothing.

49:03.023 --> 49:04.441
I can smell the chicken. Hurry up.

49:05.692 --> 49:06.777
- I can't wait.
- Hey.

49:07.277 --> 49:09.488
Do you know your neighbor upstairs?

49:09.738 --> 49:10.739
In which unit?

49:11.406 --> 49:12.491
The one above.

49:14.743 --> 49:17.162
A woman around my age
and a married couple.

49:17.746 --> 49:18.830
A married couple?

49:20.666 --> 49:22.584
Or they could just be living together.

49:23.418 --> 49:24.503
And...

49:26.922 --> 49:29.383
I don't know.
I don't cross paths with them.

49:30.258 --> 49:32.177
And I only moved here recently.

49:33.887 --> 49:34.930
Why do you ask?

49:35.555 --> 49:37.015
I just saw someone heading upstairs.

49:39.476 --> 49:40.394
It was a young guy.

49:41.812 --> 49:42.979
Not bad looking.

49:44.272 --> 49:45.273
How handsome is he?

49:46.400 --> 49:47.526
I only got a glimpse of him.

49:49.319 --> 49:52.030
Have you seen the guy
who lives with his girlfriend

49:52.739 --> 49:53.782
in the unit above?

49:56.034 --> 49:57.202
Was he that handsome?

49:57.577 --> 49:59.371
Do you want me to go and check?

50:04.000 --> 50:05.210
You know,

50:05.794 --> 50:08.672
being curious about someone
is an important sign.

50:09.840 --> 50:11.675
Your mind keeps wandering back to him.

50:12.300 --> 50:13.969
It means you're interested.

50:14.177 --> 50:15.345
If you weren't,

50:15.470 --> 50:17.889
you wouldn't care about his whereabouts.

50:20.475 --> 50:21.685
Just know this though.

50:25.105 --> 50:27.107
That qualifies as cheating too.

51:10.400 --> 51:11.359
LEE JEONG-IN

51:11.443 --> 51:13.612
I apologize for the misunderstanding.

51:34.466 --> 51:35.383
Get in.

51:37.427 --> 51:39.179
- Go back in. It's cold. See you!
- Bye.

52:11.169 --> 52:13.588
It's snowing heavily.
Have a safe trip home.

52:28.019 --> 52:30.188
Thank you for the concern.

52:42.492 --> 52:43.910
The next time it snows,

52:44.119 --> 52:46.371
we should meet outside the pharmacy.

52:46.454 --> 52:47.539
We?

53:27.787 --> 53:29.873
WOORI PHARMACY

53:43.470 --> 53:44.721
You didn't have to run.

53:46.097 --> 53:47.140
You must be cold.

53:50.852 --> 53:52.270
This is probably the best place.

53:53.438 --> 53:56.274
It won't take long.
I just have something to say.

53:57.275 --> 53:58.318
But it's cold out here.

54:00.236 --> 54:02.155
Security deactivated.

54:10.246 --> 54:11.331
Please have a seat.

54:44.197 --> 54:45.240
Thank you.

54:53.665 --> 54:55.250
I should have stuck to texting.

54:55.667 --> 54:57.377
I feel like this is a mistake.

54:58.294 --> 54:59.546
I have something to say too,

55:00.755 --> 55:01.840
Jeong-in.

55:02.590 --> 55:04.342
I have a boyfriend
who I'm planning to marry.

55:04.426 --> 55:05.427
I have a kid.

55:12.684 --> 55:13.810
You're married?

55:18.273 --> 55:19.190
Then so what?

55:23.278 --> 55:26.197
It doesn't make you
less decent or anything.

55:32.454 --> 55:33.913
Is that what you wanted to say?

55:33.997 --> 55:35.457
Of course not.

55:36.750 --> 55:38.835
Well, I guess I would have told you that
at some point.

55:44.591 --> 55:46.134
What I actually wanted to say is this.

55:48.511 --> 55:49.721
I've been curious

55:51.681 --> 55:53.641
about what kind of person you are.

55:54.601 --> 55:56.811
I have been thinking about you
since I first saw you here.

56:00.190 --> 56:02.484
I even thought of the possibility
of you being taken.

56:04.652 --> 56:05.779
Still, just once...

56:07.864 --> 56:08.990
Just once more...

56:10.492 --> 56:12.118
Well, it led me here today.

56:15.163 --> 56:16.915
It wasn't my intention,

56:19.167 --> 56:21.252
but I did make it confusing for you.

56:23.046 --> 56:25.256
- I apologize.
- Why would you?

56:25.882 --> 56:28.218
It didn't last long, but I was happy.

56:34.682 --> 56:37.477
That's probably burdening to hear.
Forget I said it.

56:39.062 --> 56:40.230
As if that's possible.

56:49.239 --> 56:50.907
I must have put you in a tough spot.

56:52.534 --> 56:53.743
Not really.

56:58.832 --> 56:59.833
Anyway,

57:00.959 --> 57:02.085
let's be friends.

57:05.630 --> 57:07.257
You don't meet people like this every day,

57:08.049 --> 57:10.093
so we can be acquaintances from now on.

57:19.853 --> 57:20.687
I'm sorry,

57:25.358 --> 57:26.860
but I won't be comfortable with that.

01:00:36.966 --> 01:00:38.509
Come on, let's go.

01:00:38.885 --> 01:00:41.346
I've been cooped up inside
ever since I got back to Korea.

01:00:41.846 --> 01:00:43.348
You're the one who secretly came back.

01:00:46.351 --> 01:00:47.852
But I'm bored, Jeong-in.

01:00:49.103 --> 01:00:51.522
It's my day off and I'd rather rest.

01:00:52.649 --> 01:00:55.485
Your boyfriend will treat me
to a welcome back dinner anyway.

01:00:56.611 --> 01:00:58.029
You've gotten more shameless.

01:00:59.030 --> 01:01:00.490
Besides, why would we go there?

01:01:00.948 --> 01:01:01.991
For fun.

01:01:03.326 --> 01:01:05.244
Fun is something you find,
not wait around for.

01:01:07.038 --> 01:01:08.790
Just don't tell people
that you're my sister.

01:01:15.213 --> 01:01:16.339
Are you really not going?

01:01:17.090 --> 01:01:18.257
I'm not.

01:01:19.384 --> 01:01:20.885
I'm holding you to that.

01:01:23.888 --> 01:01:25.056
Wait, it's snowing.

01:01:27.183 --> 01:01:28.476
It was sunny this morning though.

01:01:30.812 --> 01:01:32.188
It'll be the last snow this winter.

01:01:34.065 --> 01:01:36.317
I should find someone to hang out with

01:01:37.151 --> 01:01:39.237
since you're not interested.

01:01:41.698 --> 01:01:42.699
Let's go out.

01:01:44.534 --> 01:01:45.576
Just like that?

01:01:46.411 --> 01:01:47.662
Why the sudden change of heart?

01:01:48.162 --> 01:01:48.996
What is it?

01:01:55.503 --> 01:01:57.255
- Jae-in.
- Yes?

01:02:00.174 --> 01:02:01.217
What is it?

01:02:02.468 --> 01:02:04.011
Can you hang out with a friend?

01:02:04.762 --> 01:02:06.848
Hold on. Seriously?

01:02:07.348 --> 01:02:09.308
Are you ditching me? For whom?

01:02:09.892 --> 01:02:11.644
Well, suddenly...

01:02:14.355 --> 01:02:15.940
Forget it. It's nothing.

01:02:16.607 --> 01:02:17.734
Here comes a taxi.

01:02:31.247 --> 01:02:33.708
You sure are fearless.
This is Dad's school you're at.

01:02:33.791 --> 01:02:35.209
If you're caught, he'll kill me too.

01:02:35.293 --> 01:02:37.044
But it's a Sunday. Come on.

01:02:38.045 --> 01:02:40.339
Hey. Behave and
don't run your mouth, all right?

01:02:41.007 --> 01:02:42.508
Are you Mom? Goodness.

01:02:45.928 --> 01:02:48.473
Jeong-in, let's go over there.
There are no seats here.

01:03:06.616 --> 01:03:07.700
Jeong-in,

01:03:08.993 --> 01:03:10.787
isn't that Gi-seok?

01:03:16.918 --> 01:03:18.628
- Come on.
- Pass.

01:03:20.463 --> 01:03:22.256
- Shoot.
- Nice.

01:03:26.010 --> 01:03:27.887
- Okay.
- Here we go!

01:03:28.221 --> 01:03:29.680
Take your positions.

01:03:31.015 --> 01:03:32.308
Stop him.

01:03:32.391 --> 01:03:33.976
Get him!

01:03:34.060 --> 01:03:36.187
All right, nice!

01:03:37.438 --> 01:03:39.273
Keep it up!

01:03:40.066 --> 01:03:41.609
Defense!

01:03:56.457 --> 01:03:58.251
Watch it. Referee!

01:04:12.390 --> 01:04:13.432
Defense!

01:04:46.215 --> 01:04:48.092
- Hi.
- Gosh, it's been a while.

01:04:49.343 --> 01:04:51.637
You look happy and well.

01:04:51.721 --> 01:04:53.014
I was born to live in the wild.

01:04:53.431 --> 01:04:54.682
You're quite good at basketball.

01:04:55.725 --> 01:04:57.310
I haven't shown all of my skills yet.

01:05:48.569 --> 01:05:50.279
I find him attractive.
Isn't he attractive?

01:05:50.363 --> 01:05:53.282
You said you'll start dating again,
didn't you? Don't be so sheepish.

01:05:53.366 --> 01:05:55.493
Both sisters are gorgeous.

01:05:55.576 --> 01:05:57.495
I think Jeong-in is the prettiest one.

01:05:57.578 --> 01:05:58.996
Take care of Jeong-in instead.

01:05:59.080 --> 01:06:00.790
She's very opinionated.

01:06:00.873 --> 01:06:02.625
It's probably about us getting married.

01:06:02.708 --> 01:06:04.251
Is it marriage you hate, or just me?

01:06:04.335 --> 01:06:07.046
They say most get cold feet
when the idea is presented.

01:06:07.129 --> 01:06:08.756
But your reaction is more than that.

01:06:08.839 --> 01:06:11.342
Gi-seok, I think we need a break.

01:06:11.425 --> 01:06:12.885
I want to tell you to be selfish.

01:06:12.969 --> 01:06:14.845
You have the right to live a happy life.

01:06:14.929 --> 01:06:16.931
This is top secret.
Actually, he has a kid.

01:06:17.014 --> 01:06:18.724
If I had known,
I would've been nicer to him.

01:06:18.808 --> 01:06:21.644
Everything else is fine.
Who cares if he's a single dad?

01:06:21.727 --> 01:06:23.437
How is that fine?
What woman would like that?

01:06:23.521 --> 01:06:26.315
I've moved on,
so you don't have to worry so much.

01:06:26.816 --> 01:06:27.942
We can be friends then.

01:06:28.025 --> 01:06:29.777
What would your boyfriend say?

01:06:30.236 --> 01:06:31.445
Let's give it a shot.

01:06:31.946 --> 01:06:33.698
Let's be friends.

01:06:37.326 --> 01:06:39.328
Subtitle translation by Liya Choi
